    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just overwhelm. it's more like... what is the point? every day is the exact same cycle of seeing things we used to do together and knowing i'll never do them again. it feels so heavy. like a weight on my chest that never goes away. honestly, it feels like i'm just waiting for something to happen because there's nothing left to actually live for. does that make sense? it feels so empty.",
